results.name: Number of distinct 5th powers mod n.
comment: This sequence is multiplicative. - Leon P Smith, Apr 16 2005
link: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
S. Li, On the number of elements with maximal order in the multiplicative group modulo n, Acta Arithm. 86 (2) (1998) 113, see proof of theorem 2.1
formula: Conjecture: a(p^e) = 1+floor[(p-1)*p^(e+4)/{gcd(p-1,5)*(p^5-1)}] for primes p<>5  - _R. J. Mathar_, Oct 22 2017
program: (PARI) a(n)=my(f=factor(n)); prod(i=1, #f[, 1], my(k=f[i, 1]^f[i, 2]); #vecsort(vector(k, i, i^5%k), , 8)) \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Sep 05 2013
xref: Cf. A000224 (squares), A046530 (cubic residues), A052273 (4th powers), A052275 (6th powers), A085310 (7th powers), A085311 (8th powers), A085312 (9th powers), A085313 (10th powers), A085314 (11th powers), A228849 (12th powers).
